    <briefdescription>
<para>A <ref refid="classDali_1_1Accessibility_1_1Socket" kindref="compound">Socket</ref> is the root of the AT-SPI tree that can be embedded as a subtree in the tree belonging to another process (the Plug). The Plug initiates the Plug-Socket connection by calling <ref refid="classDali_1_1Accessibility_1_1Socket_1ae33ab416982f9cd4b809dfaea890cf2b" kindref="member">Embed()</ref> and terminates it by calling <ref refid="classDali_1_1Accessibility_1_1Socket_1aafffae512b7c98f574be0447b58ece72" kindref="member">Unembed()</ref>. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>See AT_SPI2_CORE/xml/Socket.xml for a description of this interface in XML format. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
